import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='Median delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'], vert=False)
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():0.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    origin_counts = data.groupby('origin').count().reset_index()
    origin_counts = origin_counts[['origin', 'count']]
    origin_counts = origin_counts.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(origin_counts['origin'], origin_counts['count'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by origin?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay')
    ax.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;
